remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that bundles the parameters accepted by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. Use it to create
a customized copy of an existing typeface by specifying a variation design
position, a color palette index, per-entry palette overrides, or a font
collection index.

Because this is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or captured in
lambdas. Build the arguments, call `Clone`, and let the struct go out of scope.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create a narrow, italic variation of a variable font with a custom palette.
var position = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFontManager.TagFromFamilyName("wdth"), Value = 75 },
};

var overrides = new SKFontPaletteOverride[]
{
    new SKFontPaletteOverride { Index = 0, Color = (uint)SKColors.DarkSlateBlue },
};

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = position,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    PaletteOverrides = overrides,
};

using var customFace = typeface.Clone(args);
```
